rComments: bad prof all around. first time teaching. wouldn't recommend

Il est définitivement un de mes profs préférés! Il n'hésite pas de prendre une tangente en classe si nécessaire. Les examens sont exactement la matière enseigné en classe. J'ai eu plusieurs problèmes ce semestre et c'est le seul prof qui a pris le temps de m'écouter et m'aider. Il tient à la réussite de ces étudiants!
Un excellent prof! Il donne une chance pour améliorer ta note et prends son temps pour bien expliquer la matière. Très drôle et charmant! Aide les étudiants beaucoup s'il voit que tu travail fort!

Great prof and really cares about his students. Go to class because he will literally give you questions from the exam. If you don't attend class you propably wont do super well on the midterm / final as some of his questions are specific to things explained in class. Textbook is great to review concepts. Exam/final is MC. Overall would recommend!

Great prof! He conveys the material very well and it's clear he cares about his students' success. He's open to going off track and starting interesting discussions with the group and his exams are very fair.

Il récompense les étudiants qui viennent au cours en leur donant des indices sur l'examen. Il explique très bien la matière, répond aux questions en classe et fait participer la classe. Ces examens sont plus que fair.
My favorite professor this semester! He is clear and is not afraid to go back over the material if asked. His exams are fair, he tells you exactly what to study. His sens of humour is incredible!
Excellent choix! Ne parle pas trop vite!!! ;-D Il veut vraiment le succès de ses élèves et va répéter quelque chose 100x s'il le faut!
One of my favorite teachers at uottawa. He has a good sense of humor while teaching and you can tell he cares about his students success.

C'est mon 2e cours avec lui et je ne pas peux demander mieux! Il est vraiment super comme prof! Il hésite pas à répéter la matière plusieurs fois, fait participer la classe en posant des questions, et guide notre étude lorsqu'il enseigne. Il a même créé un guide d'étude cette session!! Il parle vite des fois, mais à pat de ça, j'adore son style!!

Beaucoup de matière et beaucoup de biologie. Si tu n'as jamais eu de cours de bio auparemment je ne te recommande pas puisque c'est beaucoup de travail lorsque tu pars pratiquement à zéro. Il dit beaucoup de définition en classe et parle très vite. Il a de la difficulté lui-même a utiliser le vocabulaire qu'il utilise dans la matière du cours.

He is one the most authentic professors I have never met. He does not hesitate to repeat class material when asked, he constantly engages with students, explains the same concept in different ways and stays after class to answer questions from students. Definitely an amazing professors!

He was fantastic! He was able to deliver the course material with such at ease. He did not hesitate to repeat 100 times the same thing. You could tell he wanted the best for his students. As some have said, he got sometimes confused, but overall, one of my best professors at uOttawa.

This teacher is by far one of the best at uOttawa. It was his 1st year teaching, but makes his lectures amazing by being funny and caring. He will repeat the same concept over and over again until the class understands. He also gives a lot of hints for his exams. He does make a few mistakes in his explanations, but he corrects himself immediately.
Good prof!
Très bon prof! Il prend de temps de s'assurer que tous comprennent et il n'y a aucune surprise à l'examen.
bad prof all around. first time teaching. wouldn't recommend.
Loved him! If he has to repeat something 50x in order for his students to understand he will. If you have somewhat a background in biology (grade 12 biology) this should be an easy class for you!

I am graduating this semester and he was the best professor I had! You could tell he was passionate by the topic and made sure that everyone in class would understand. He clearly wants his students to succeeded. It was his first time teaching but he was definitely very good at his job!

The prof gives bonus questions on the exams and he will give out a couple exam questions. However, the prof makes many mistakes and only notices if a student points it out. His teaching is all over the place. Get ready to teach yourself the class . He does not ensure everyone understands, as long as 1/4 of the class understands he will move on.

It was very clear that this is his first time teaching a class. He jumps from one section to another, he is all over the place, he contradicts himself or the powerpoint very often, making the subject matter even more complicated. You're better off learning from the book. He does however gives bonus questions and rewards students who come to class..

Tu vois qu'il est passionné de la neuroscience. Il fera tout pour la réussite des élèves. Si tu te présentes au cours il récompense les étudiants en donnant des indices de ce qui retrouve sur l'examen. Les examens réflètent grandement la matière, aucune surprise. Je reprendrais ce professeur n'importe quand!
Loved this teacher!! I think it was his first time teaching a class, but it's a good prof and makes it clear what you need to study for, which he specifies in class. Recommended x10000

It's his first time teaching, but he really does an amazing job! He's hilarious and knows how to make a bio class interesting and captivating. He doesn't hesitate to explain several times class material when asked and doesn't make you fell dump. On some occasions ,he makes mistakes when he explains, but he corrects himself right away.
